Phase 8: Couple Match (mutual pose interest, only matches revealed)

- schema.sql: pose_interests table (couple_id, member, pose_id) with
  per-member RLS so a partner can read only their own rows; a security-
  definer pose_matches(couple) RPC returns only poses both partners
  want. Re-runnable; owner must re-run the updated schema.
- PartnerBackend.setPoseInterest/poseMatches (InMemory + Supabase).
- PartnerRepository.sharePoseInterest broadcasts a want-to-try to all
  couples; refreshMatches computes matches per couple, caches matched
  pose ids and tracks already-seen matches (persisted) so only newly
  appeared matches are surfaced.
- Pose detail: marking want-to-try shares interest (best-effort) and
  reveals a discreet match dialog naming the partner; unmarking removes
  the interest and the match. Catalog badges matched poses with a heart
  and shows a snackbar for new matches found on open.
- Stealth-guarded; unrequited picks are never shown to the partner.
- 84 host tests green (incl. mutual-only and remove-interest cases).

Note: real-time push when the partner matches while you're away needs
FCM (not built); matches surface on next open/toggle. Recorded for owner.

